t to the existing 5.0.0 setup: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. Tests can exercise normal usage by creating Vertx.vertx(), starting an in-process HttpServer on 127.0.0.1 with an ephemeral port, and using WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient against it; no external service is required.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"OAuth2WebClient references the optional io.vertx:vertx-auth-oauth2 dependency; avoid OAuth2-specific coverage unless adding that dependency is intentionally in scope.\",\n    \"The unsafe-access properties are tied to the Java 25/Netty 4.2.x native runtime behavior, so local Gradle and Native Image verification should remain authoritative.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_072cb656e58c16cf016a3f0e7e2e9c81948af3761404da3049\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1050, "output": 808, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26946, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782517365244, "responseId": "resp_072cb656e58c16cf016a3f0e75b7f88194be8009ddf7f82c5c"}}
